track.name: My Funny Valentine
comments: recorded live @ lincoln center philharmonic hall 1964...miles (tpt)...herbie hancock (p)...ron carter (db)...george coleman (ts)...tony williams (d)...
great. i'll be late for work. again. thanks, miles.
Miles Davis in Concert version is incredible
keeps it going time after time after time after time.sweet.
makes me feel at home in that corner of the cocktail lounge, smoke filled room.
super job with this classic! miles forever.
Actually Red Garland plays piano on this album. Along with the  Relaxin', Workin', and Steamin' albums.
This is the best sad song ever
There is so much broken longing in this version that I forget about Chet.
